				<a href="http://www.zerto.com/"><span class="et_pb_image_wrap"><img src="/wp-content/uploads/zerto-red-on-white-logo-2.gif" alt="" /></span></a>
			</div><div class="et_pb_text et_pb_module et_pb_bg_layout_light et_pb_text_align_left ntl-full-column et_pb_text_0">
				
				
				<div class="et_pb_text_inner">
					<p class="p4"><span class="s2">Business continuity solutions</span></p>
				</div>
			</div> <!-- .et_pb_text --><div class="et_pb_text et_pb_module et_pb_bg_layout_light et_pb_text_align_left ntl-full-column et_pb_text_1">
				
				
				<div class="et_pb_text_inner">
					<p class="p4"><span class="s2">InterVision partners with Zerto as a premier leader because of its innovative enterprise-class disaster recovery and business continuity software that is specifically designed for virtualized data centers and cloud environments. Zerto runs under the hood of InterVision&#8217;s DRaaS solution. Â </span></p>
<p class="p4"><span class="s2">Zertoâs <a href="http://www.zerto.com/about/awards/"><span class="s3">award winning solution</span></a> provides enterprises with continuous data replication &amp; recovery designed specifically for virtualized infrastructure and the cloud. <a href="http://www.zerto.com/products/enterprise/"><span class="s3">Zerto Virtual Replication</span></a> is the industryâs first hypervisor-based replication solution for tier-one applications, replacing traditional array-based BC/DR solutions that were not built to deal with the virtual paradigm.</span></p>
<p class="p4"><span class="s2">Today, enterprises of all sizes are deploying applications on virtualized IT infrastructures and clouds. The values of virtualization including flexibility, scalability and mobility can complicate business continuity efforts in times of disaster. The advantages of virtualization can be in conflict with your ability to recover the business in the event of disaster. Not so with Zertoâs virtual-friendly continuous data replication. </span></p>
<p class="p4"><strong><span class="s2">Learn more at <a href="http://www.zerto.com/"><span class="s4">www.zerto.com</span></a></span></strong></p>
				</div>
			</div> <!-- .et_pb_text -->
			</div> <!-- .et_pb_column -->
				
				
			</div> <!-- .et_pb_row -->
				
			</div> <!-- .et_pb_section --><div class="et_pb_section  et_pb_section_2 et_pb_with_background et_section_regular et_section_transparent">
				
				
				
					<div class=" et_pb_row et_pb_row_2">
				<div class="et_pb_column et_pb_column_4_4  et_pb_column_2 et_pb_css_mix_blend_mode_passthrough et-last-child">
				
				
				<div class="et_pb_promo et_pb_module et_pb_bg_layout_dark et_pb_text_align_left  et_pb_cta_0" style="background-color: rgba(126,190,197,0);">
				
				
				<div class="et_pb_promo_description">
					<h2 class="et_pb_module_header">Masters of Disasters</h2>
					<p class="p4"><span class="s2">When you canât afford a disaster, be sure to have a solid DR/BC plan. InterVisionâs DRaaS was designed using Zertoâs replication and disaster recovery toolsets. Zerto drives down RPO and RTO objectives. </span></p>
				</div>
				<div class="et_pb_button_wrapper"><a class="et_pb_promo_button et_pb_button" href="/solutions-services/cloud-services/disaster-recovery-as-a-service/">Learn More</a></div>
