				<div class="et_pb_column et_pb_column_4_4  et_pb_column_1 et_pb_css_mix_blend_mode_passthrough et-last-child">
				
				
				<div class="et_pb_module et_pb_image et-waypoint et_animated et_pb_image_0 et_always_center_on_mobile">
				
				
				<a href="http://www.commvault.com"><span class="et_pb_image_wrap"><img src="/wp-content/uploads/commvault.jpg" alt="commvault" /></span></a>
			</div><div class="et_pb_text et_pb_module et_pb_bg_layout_light et_pb_text_align_left ntl-full-column et_pb_text_0">
				
				
				<div class="et_pb_text_inner">
					<p class="p2"><span class="s1">Backup and Recovery</span></p>
				</div>
			</div> <!-- .et_pb_text --><div class="et_pb_text et_pb_module et_pb_bg_layout_light et_pb_text_align_left ntl-full-column et_pb_text_1">
				
				
				<div class="et_pb_text_inner">
					<p class="p1"><span class="s1">Enterprise data is anything but uniform. Which is why your data protection, backup and recovery solution needs to cover the full range of data sources, file types, storage media and backup modes â from snapshots to streaming.Â </span></p>
<p class="p1"><span class="s1">With all that diversity, you want control over your data, however the last thing you want to maintain is a separate solution for each distinct backup and recovery requirement. With Commvault, your requirements are met. With their integrated automated data protection approach, you have one complete view of all your stored data regardless of its location.</span></p>
<p class="p4"><span class="s1">For their reliability, consistency and ability to innovate, Commvault was named a leader in Gartnerâs Magic Quadrant for Enterprise Backup Software and Integrated Appliances seven years in a row. They support data on-premise or in the cloud and are the core of InterVision&#8217;s Backup as a Service solution, supporting more than 25 cloud storage platforms.</span></p>
<p class="p2"><span class="s1">Some organizations standardize on a single DBMS, while other support a range of databases from SQL Server to PostgreSQL. To Commvault, it doesnât matter as it simplifies backup and disaster recovery across all of your databases.</span></p>
<p class="p2"><span class="s1">With 60% of business critical information stored in email (source: IDC), users can use Commvaultâs self-service access to search and restore messages without IT intervention. And with built-in application aware snapshot support and software deduplication, Commvault keeps your users productive and happy.</span></p>
<p>Don&#8217;t let your data protection infrastructure is hold you back.</p>
<p><strong>Find out more atÂ <a href="https://www.commvault.com/">www.commvault.com</a></strong></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
